## Background Work

{% if use_background_jobs %}
Background jobs are part of the intended design. Use them for notifications, import/export pipelines, and long-running orchestration. Do not keep request handlers open while work that can be queued is in progress.
{% else %}
No background worker is assumed at the scaffold level. Add one only when request latency or workflow complexity justifies it.
{% endif %}

## Operational Notes

{% if use_redis %}
- Redis is available for caching, coordination, or worker support.
{% else %}
- No cache or broker is assumed yet; keep initial complexity low.
{% endif %}
{% if use_docker %}
- Docker is part of the intended local and deployment workflow.
{% else %}
